1
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,520
I hear she lives alone in that run-down house.

2
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:46,240
Not scared of ghosts knocking at midnight?

3
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,600
What ghosts, though?

4
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:52,200
The short-lived wretch her mom stabbed.

5
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:53,960
Hey!

6
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:54,960
Little murderer.

7
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,200
You bumped into me.

8
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,400
Apologize to me, damn it.

9
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,440
The nerve of you, still eating here.

10
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,240
You've gone and dirtied the stool.

11
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,240
Exactly.

12
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,840
Why are so many dogs barking today?

13
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,960
So noisy.

14
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:09,720
You...

15
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,520
Who are you calling a dog?

16
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,200
Boss, the usual.

17
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,400
Alright.

18
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:13,960
Sit.

19
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,360
Chen Baixi, mind your own business.

20
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,000
And if I don't, what then?

21
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,360
Li Yiran is family to us.

22
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,280
When it comes to family,

23
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,520
of course I'll step in.

24
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:25,040
You...

25
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,040
Forget it, forget it.

26
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,680
What bad luck.

27
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,960
Lately, I read a line in a book

28
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,720
that really made a lot of sense

29
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:58,040
A lion does not turn back at the barking of dogs

30
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,040
Just think about it

31
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,840
If a lion beats a pack of mad dogs,

32
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,120
is that glorious?

33
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,520
No, it's not

34
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,680
It's beneath its dignity

35
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:16,840
Thank you

36
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,600
Exactly

37
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,000
Yiran, have you ever heard a saying?

38
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,440
Life is a tragedy when seen in close-up,

39
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,160
but a comedy in long-shot.

40
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:33,280
It all depends on how you look at it.

41
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,040
Here

42
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,280
Grab a bun

43
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,000
Run!

44
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,880
Big bear! Big bear!

45
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:54,400
Let's go, hurry!

46
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,480
Run! Run! Run!

47
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,560
Run, run!

48
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,080
Yiran! Yiran!

49
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:28,920
Hello, Auntie Lan.

50
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,960
Hello.

51
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,520
Why'd you run off so fast?

52
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,320
I still wanted to say hi to you.

53
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,120
You scared me to death!

54
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:40,080
So the acting you studied in Beijing,

55
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,520
it was animal acting?

56
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,960
So? Did I look convincing?

57
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:44,840
Wasn't it super realistic?

58
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,240
Way too realistic!

59
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,000
You scared us both half to death.

60
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,960
She even took a tumble, you know.

61
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,080
I gotta say,

62
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,240
I really thought

63
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,160
this bear had escaped from the zoo.

64
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,040
It's so lifelike.

65
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,680
Are these teeth real or fake?

66
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,520
Feel them for yourself.

67
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,640
The tongue's even soft.

68
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,080
Oh my, it's got drool too!

69
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:17,960
So realistic!

70
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,520
It nipped my hand red, damn it!

71
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,480
Chen Xiaofang, are you nuts?

72
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,400
What kind of job is this you found?

73
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,920
Coming to the zoo to play an animal!

74
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,560
Well, my brother couldn't find anyone,

75
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,320
and your mom couldn't find work,

76
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,840
so you hit the jackpot.

77
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,080
What a coincidence, right?

78
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,240
Get lost.

79
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,080
Coincidence my ass.

80
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,120
You and your brother are both unreliable.

81
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,520
Blood is thicker than water, I guess.

82
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,160
Bro,

83
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:56,880
you've looked so miserable lately.

84
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,960
Is the zoo short on people?

85
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,320
I recently set up

86
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,040
a Cute Pet Paradise to make some money.

87
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,920
I wanted someone to dress up as a bear,

88
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,120
but nobody's willing to do it.

89
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,520
So I've had to do it myself.

90
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:14,520
It's stressful, exhausting, and miserable.

91
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,160
Then this is perfect!

92
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,520
I've got two unemployed talents right here.

93
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,360
Who?

94
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,960
My bestie and her mom.

95
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:24,920
You mean Li Yiran and Auntie Lan?

96
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:25,480
Exactly.

97
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,120
No, no, no.

98
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,360
This job's grueling,

99
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,600
and you have to play it convincingly.

100
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,640
How could those two ever pull this off?

101
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:36,240
Aren't you the acting master?

102
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,120
Just teach them, problem solved.

103
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:41,960
Come on, bro,

104
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,680
just help me out.

105
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:44,960
They can't find work,

106
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:45,880
you can't find anyone,

107
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,320
it's fate.

108
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:53,640
Fine, I'll give it a shot.

109
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:04,840
Auntie Lan, I never expected you to be this good.

110
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,240
What did I do to deserve this?

111
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,240
What did I do to deserve this?

112
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,400
Getting to play a bear in this lifetime.

113
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,680
Fur Softener.

114
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,280
You spray this on, right?

115
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,240
Yeah, once you spray it,

116
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,640
the fur gets smoother.

117
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,840
I've got a question.

118
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,960
You said it's got drool,

119
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,240
so does it have tears too?

120
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,840
That, we don't have yet.

121
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,960
Didn't you study acting?

122
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,800
Are you the type

123
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,320
who can cry on command?

124
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,360
Let me tell you,

125
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:40,160
the second the director yells "three, two, one, action,"

126
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,480
my tears just come right out.

127
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,640
Really?

128
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,080
Really.

129
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,160
Then cry for me right now.

130
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,240
Right now?

131
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,120
Actually, we've got something else.

132
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,440
What's that?

133
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,560
If you can't cry,

134
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,440
you can use this.

135
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:56,720
What is it?

136
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,760
Don't keep me in suspense.

137
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,520
A tear stick

138
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,760
Whenever you can't cry

139
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,720
you just take this tear stick

140
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,280
and rub it under your eyelids

141
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,440
Rub it right here

142
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,880
just like a lip balm

143
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,040
Let me try it

144
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:12,560
Go ahead

145
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,080
So cold, so cold, so cold

146
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:15,720
On the eyelids

147
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:17,840
So cold, so cold

148
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,280
Then you keep your eyes open, staring at one spot

149
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,480
I can't, I can't

150
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,440
This feels awful

151
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,320
But this thing

152
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,200
It looks like lipstick, pretty cute actually

153
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,200
It's yours now

154
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:30,760
Really?

155
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:31,360
Really

156
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,960
You're so generous

157
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,160
Then I'll take it

158
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:34,960
Go on, take it

159
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,000
Thank you

160
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,720
You're welcome

161
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:43,360
Lend me this to play around with

162
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:50,880
You ready?

163
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,120
Yiran.

164
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,880
Jobs are hard to find these days.

165
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:58,000
You'll work alongside Auntie Lan for a while.

166
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,200
Once she settles in,

167
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,680
I'll have my brother keep an eye on her for you.

168
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,800
This job's simple and stable.

169
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,760
So you won't have to worry when you go back to Shanghai.

170
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,360
Simple.

171
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,320
Stable.

172
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:08,800
Yeah.

173
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,000
What are you doing? You scared me!

174
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,280
Why'd you hang up?

175
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,880
See? I'm the one who's good to you.

176
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,360
I'd never hang up on you.

177
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,680
Isn't it cute? Isn't it cute?

178
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,640
Cute my ass.

179
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:25,600
Take that head off right now.

180
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,600
I just wanted to get used to it early.

181
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,280
You don't need to get used to it.

182
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:34,520
Dressing as a bear to fool kids.

183
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:36,000
You can't do this job. Let's go.

184
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,120
Who says this is fooling kids?

185
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,520
How can you call this fooling anyone?

186
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,080
Our Here Comes Baby Bear program

187
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,640
is all about creating a dream for children.

188
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,960
We want kids to spend a magical, wonderful day

189
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:51,600
here in our paradise.

190
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,640
Right, Baixi?

191
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:53,880
Right.

192
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,840
Director Ding.

193
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,400
Yeah.

194
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,080
After hearing you describe this job,

195
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,440
I feel so excited!

196
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:02,720
Right?

197
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,600
It's so much fun!

198
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,880
This job is so sacred!

199
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,640
You just can't afford real animals, that's all.

200
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,640
Making it sound so noble.

201
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,200
You're deceiving your visitors, you know that?

202
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,640
Now, young lady,

203
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:12,400
you can't put it that way.

204
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,840
Think about it. If a real bear

205
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,480
interacted with kids, how dangerous would that be?

206
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:17,800
Besides,

207
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,040
feeding and caring for one costs money.

208
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,200
Our current income

209
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,520
isn't even enough to buy its feed.

210
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,280
That's really how it is.

211
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,480
When she was little, she ate and drank a ton,

212
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,640
and needed diapers too.

213
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:31,680
The little money I earned

214
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:33,120
was never enough for her.

215
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,600
Right?

216
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,560
Who asked you, Wu Huilan?

217
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,080
If you can't make comparisons, don't.

218
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,200
Why compare me to an animal?

219
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,280
So you see,

220
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,520
this brings joy to the kids,

221
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,200
brings in money for the park,

222
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,840
and pays your wages.

223
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,480
That's three birds with one stone!

224
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,760
Thanks, Director Ding.

225
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,200
But we won't be considering this job.

226
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:51,800
Give the stuff back to him.

227
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:56,640
Actually, this is a plan to save animals.

228
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,000
Save what animals?

229
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,360
Oh my god.

230
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,040
These animals are so pitiful!

231
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,640
Yeah.

232
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,240
The vast majority of animals here

233
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,520
are malnourished.

234
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,200
Some are sick, some are dying.

235
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,800
And nobody takes care of them?

236
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,920
The director only cares about making money.

237
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,720
Why would he care whether the animals live or die?

238
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,440
You mean that Director Ding just now?

239
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,240
That heartless devil, why won't he help?

240
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,520
The economy's been bad these past two years.

241
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,280
Tickets are ten yuan each,

242
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,520
and fewer than ten visitors come each day.

243
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,760
We've been losing money the whole time.

244
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,360
Large animals cost money in every way.

245
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,000
We can't even afford to keep them.

246
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,240
But you still can't just

247
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,440
stand by and watch

248
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,560
these animals wait to die!

249
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:49,920
Look at this tiger.

250
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:51,160
It's old,

251
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,080
and it's sick.

252
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,360
The director says treating it is pointless.

253
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,960
He plans to put it down.

254
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,600
That's just inhumane.

255
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,080
They want to euthanize it.

256
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,120
An animal's life is a life too.

257
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,000
Am I right or what?

258
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:11,400
So recently,

259
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,040
I made a Here Comes Baby Bear rescue plan.

260
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,840
I set up a new Cute Pet Paradise.

261
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,240
To draw kids in for a hands-on experience.

262
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,480
That way, once we make money,

263
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,960
we can buy them food,

264
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,440
and afford to treat them, too.

265
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,360
Another busybody sticking their nose in.

266
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,040
How is this being a busybody?

267
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,680
I don't think I'm meddling at all.

268
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,320
Now I get it.

269
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,720
You want us to dress up as bears,

270
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,720
really just to save them.

271
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,520
Right?

272
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,320
Exactly.

273
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,040
It's a last-ditch effort, that's all.

274
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:42,680
Save one if we can, one at a time.

275
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:43,960
Nobody's dying here!

276
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,840
A bad life is better than a good death.

277
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,840
We've got to live on properly.

278
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,640
And let them live on properly too.

279
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,680
Yiran and I are both caring people.

280
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,520
Aren't we?

281
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,440
She didn't say no, so that's a yes.

282
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,960
This job,

283
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,400
we'll take it.

284
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,440
That's really wonderful!

285
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,240
Auntie Lan,

286
